title: Six contestants #BeatBrian in Week 8
text:
Six contestants #BeatBrian in Week 8 BRIAN ACHATZ, bachatz@pnj.com 4:01 p.m. CDT October 19, 2015 Find out which six participants #BeatBrian this week. (Photo: Ben Twingley) 17 CONNECT 1 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Welp... I guess I'll admit I got a little cocky after beating all participants in Week 7. 
I had a decent week, missing two games in an eight-game slate. 
I missed Taylor County over Catholic, and like many of the 73 participants last week, I was heartbroken by Pensacola High's one-point loss to Arnold. 
Six participants beat me, but it was only Juliet Wingate who showed an outstanding 8-0 week. 
Fittingly so, Wingate won the raffle for the weekly grand prize (#BeatBrian t-shirt, tervis tumbler, $25 gift card). 
Four other winners won the drawing for a one of a kind, Andy Marlette custom-designed #BeatBrian shirt â€” congratulations to Darryl Randolph, Raymond Stewart, Brandon Moberly and Wayne Rushing. 
Winners are welcome to come by the Pensacola News Journal (2 North Palafox Street) beginning Wednesday to claim their prizes. 
Hard to believe Week 9 is already here, so make sure you get to www.pnj.com/BeatBrian before 5 p.m. Thursday to sign up for this week's competition. 
It feels like nearly everyone is on the road, or off this week as there are just three games in town this Friday night. 
The Pine Forest will get their shot at the prestigious Niceville Eagles, which should provide a great test before the District 1-6A championship game vs. Tate the following week. 
West Florida will seek to keep it going in District 1-5A competition after knocking off undefeated Bay last Friday. 
Here are the games for Week 9: 
Friday, Oct. 23 
Jay at Rocky Bayou Christian, 7 p.m. 
Northview at Walton, 7 p.m. 
West Florida at Arnold, 7 p.m. 
Tate at Choctaw, 7 p.m. 
Mosley at PHS, 7:30 p.m. 
Washington at Catholic, 7:30 p.m. 
Niceville at Pine Forest, 7:30 p.m.
